The number of unrewarded visits was affected by health status (P = 0.013) and day (P < 0.001; Figure 1
). Calves with NCD performed fewer unrewarded visits than healthy calves on d −2 (P = 0.007), −1 (P = 0.055), and 0 (P = 0.025). We noted a health status × day interaction for volume of milk consumed (P = 0.001; Figure 2
); calves with NCD drank less on d −4 (P = 0.012), −2 (P = 0.044), −1 (P = 0.053), and 0 (P < 0.001) than healthy calves.
